comments.body:
So, I tried adding a test to text_test.dart, and I'm perplexed.  Why does this fail at the expect for `largeSize.height`?  It thinks that text with scale factor 3.0 is the same size as text with a scale of 1.0 (14 px).

```dart
  testWidgets('Text respects textScaleFactor', (WidgetTester tester) async {
    await tester.pumpWidget(const Center(
        child: const Text('Hello', textScaleFactor: 3.0, textDirection: TextDirection.ltr)
    ));

    final RichText text = tester.firstWidget(find.byType(RichText));
    expect(text.textScaleFactor, 3.0);
    final Size largeSize = tester.getSize(find.byType(RichText));
    expect(largeSize.height, equals(3.0 * 14.0));
  });
```
Is this some issue with the Linux engine vs the regular engine?  Because text is clearly scaled on a device.  I just can't see how paragraph layout could work on the tests if it can't reliably determine the text size.

Note that this doesn't even involve MediaQuery, so it doesn't have anything to do with that.

